Al Baraka Banking Group, Etisalat and Zain: Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-03-23T04:52:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/al-baraka-banking-group-etisalat-and-zain-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  The Dubai Financial Market General Index rose 1 percent to
1,521.1.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  gained 0.6 percent, while
 Saudi Arabia ’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  fell 0.2 percent.       Al Baraka Banking Group BSC (BARKA BI): Bahrain’s biggest
publicly traded lender will seek shareholders approval to sell
$300 million of Islamic bonds. The shares retreated 1.5 percent
to $1.35 when they last traded on March 20.       Emirates Telecommunications Corp. (ETISALAT UH): The United
Arab Emirates’ biggest phone company had its long-term foreign
and domestic currency ratings confirmed at Aa3 by Moody’s
Investors Service. Moody’s had placed the ratings on review for
possible downgrade. The shares were unchanged at 11 dirhams.  Mobile Telecommunications Co. (ZAIN KK): The Kuwaiti phone
company known as Zain signed a $1.3 billion syndicated loan
which was increased from an initial $1.2 billion targeted in
January, two people with knowledge of the deal said. The shares
were unchanged at 1,320 fils.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
